A former Kaduna Central Senator, Shehu Sani, has reacted to the killing of Justice Stanley Nnaji, a former Judge of the Enugu State High court, by unknown gunmen. DAILY POST had reported that he was shot in the chest and robbed of his SUV by men in a mask in Enugu on Monday. The assailants, numbering three, double-crossed the former Judge along the Ebeano Tunnel, Enugu, dragged him out and drove his car away after killing him. Confirming the development, Daniel Ndukwe, the Enugu State Police spokesman, in a statement released, said the gunmen trailed Nnaji from an unknown location to where they shot him and took his car away. “The victim was rushed to the hospital, where he was confirmed dead by doctors on duty and deposited in the mortuary for autopsy. Reacting, Sani, in a tweet his handle on Monday, described Nnaji’s death as tragic and condemnable. He also asked God to console Nnaji’s family and colleagues. Sani tweeted, “The report of the killing of Justice Stanley Nnaji in Enugu by Unknown Gunmen (UG), is tragic and condemnable. May his soul Rest In. “My condolences to his family and colleagues.” Also reacting, Reno Omokri, a former presidential aide, tweeted, ” A judge killed in broad daylight. Herdsmen killed 9 in Enugu and killed a pregnant woman in Nasarawa. “A Presidential candidate is shot. Unknown number of Nigerians abducted by bandits in Zamfara. All happened today. Nigeria under @MBuhari is a plane without a pilot.” Kidnapped Plateau State University student released 